      <mads:note type="source">"Cydias, 2, one of the early Greek poets, whom Plutarch ...classes
      together with Mimnermus and Archilochus....."
      Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 1 1870, p. 910</mads:note>
      <mads:note type="source">Cydias, Erotic poet, quotes from Pl. Chrm. 155d, mentioned by Plut. Mor.
      931e. He was obviously popular in Athens as he is depicted as a komast on a red-figured dish
      (Munich 2614) and on a psykter (London, BM E767) from c. 500 BC [1. 12-13]. Robbins, Emmet
      (Toronto); Weißenberger, Michael (Greifswald); Hoesch, Nicola (München); Nutton, Vivian
      (London). "Cydias." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth
      Schneider . Brill, 2007. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 23 July 2007</mads:note>
